FBIS4-39236 "drsov109_b_94011" FBIS-SOV-94-109 Daily Report 7 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Central Bank Tightens Currency Exchange Control Central Bank Tightens Currency Exchange Control LD0706095894 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 0400 GMT 7 Jun 94 LD0706095894 Moscow Russian Television Network Russian BFN [From the "Vesti" newscast] [Text] A spokesman for the Bank of Russia says that the central bank intends to tighten its control of currency exchange points because many contraventions of banking legislation are taking place. Among other things, an upper limit will be imposed on cash sales of hard currency -- probably this summer. However, he added that this question must be agreed with the Government and the customs service.
